## Acceptance criteria

* `run_support_analysis()` (or equivalent) implements the full Support Agent runtime pipeline
* Pipeline consumes sanitized thread context from Step 9.5, not only a single `customer_message`
* Pipeline returns schema-valid `SupportInsights` from Step 9.4
* `reply_drafts[]` contains safe drafts with per-draft approval metadata
* Support themes and sentiment are summarized without PII leakage
* Step 9.1 approval policy is applied to every generated draft
* Step 9.2 refusal/scope guardrails run before draft generation where applicable
* Step 9.3 prompt-injection defenses protect untrusted customer message text
* Step 9.4 schema validation and Step 9.5 sanitized context behavior are preserved
* `AI_OUTPUT_LANGUAGE` is supported for user-facing summaries and reply text where practical
* Empty/no-message cases are handled deterministically without hallucinating customer facts
* Focused deterministic tests cover normal threads, empty threads, sensitive requests, refusal cases, and prompt-injection scenarios without real LLM API keys
* No real external side effects, Django DB access from agents, Prestia-specific hardcoding, or raw PII in fixtures/logs
* Steps 9.7–9.8 are not implemented in this step
* `docs/phases/step-9.6.md` documents the implementation
